touch file.sh --> to create a file ( imp in automation)
man <any command> --> discribe the command in detail
vi/vim <filename> --> to edit a file
cat <filename> --> print content of the file
./filename or sh filename.sh --> to execute the script
chmod --> changes permissions
top --> lists all the process that are running currently
df --> printing disk space
free --> getting free space info
nproc--> number of CPUs
set -x --> turn on debug mode( show the commands which are being executed)
ps -ef --> list of the process in full format with all details
